And whenever possible, we source locally from farmer's markets, ranches, and purveyors who shop locally. "Local produce is delivered six days a week, because we have no freezers. I make a lot things from scratch-- granola, dressings, jams, ketchup, mayonnaise, aiolis-- just to name few. One, a fisherman , the other a craft beer brewer, and both watermen, did the only reasonable thing: They went sailing. And they hatched the idea for the Venice Ale House. It was critical that ingredients for the menu be organic, sustainable and locally sourced whenever possible. the beverage list should be local too. After all, why ship beer and wine half way around the world when we can support great breweries and wineries right here in California?
